Document: CameraFeed
Path: godot/classes/class_camerafeed.rst
Summary: Provides access to the camera feed for AR/VR applications.

CameraFeed

Inherits: Resource < RefCounted < Object

Base class for camera feed resources used in AR/VR applications. It provides access to the camera feed for rendering and tracking purposes.

This class is intended to be inherited by specific camera feed implementations, such as those for ARKit or OpenXR. It defines the common interface for accessing camera data and properties.

Properties:
active (bool): Whether the camera feed is currently active and providing data.
texture (Texture2D): The texture containing the camera feed image.
transform (Transform3D): The transform of the camera in the AR/VR world space.

Methods:
get_active_texture() → Texture2D: Returns the active texture of the camera feed.
get_camera_transform() → Transform3D: Returns the current transform of the camera.
get_feed_texture() → Texture2D: Returns the texture containing the camera feed image.
get_projection_matrix() → Projection: Returns the projection matrix for the camera.
get_texture_transform() → Transform2D: Returns the transform of the camera feed texture.
is_active() → bool: Checks if the camera feed is active.
start() → void: Starts the camera feed.
stop() → void: Stops the camera feed.
---CHUNK---
