Document: CameraFeed
Path: godot/classes/class_camerafeed.rst
Summary: Provides access to a physical camera feed on a device, capturing frames for use in Godot.
A camera feed gives you access to a single physical camera attached to your device. When enabled, Godot will start capturing frames from the camera which can then be used. See also CameraServer.

Note: Many cameras will return YCbCr images which are split into two textures and need to be combined in a shader. Godot does this automatically for you if you set the environment to show the camera image in the background.

Note: This class is currently only implemented on Linux, Android, macOS, and iOS. On other platforms no CameraFeeds will be available. To get a CameraFeed on iOS, the camera plugin from godot-ios-plugins is required.
---CHUNK---
Document: CameraFeed
Path: godot/classes/class_camerafeed.rst
Summary: Defines the properties of the CameraFeed class, including its active state, transform, and supported formats.

Properties:
* feed_is_active (bool): Indicates if the camera feed is currently active. Default: false
* feed_transform (Transform2D): The transformation matrix applied to the camera feed. Default: Transform2D(1, 0, 0, -1, 0, 1)
* formats (Array): An array listing the supported image formats for the camera feed. Default: []
